+# Phase 9.4 — commit-tree options
+
+## Goal
+
+Port and pass `git/t/t1100-commit-tree-options.sh` in `./tests`, then make `gust commit-tree` green for the port.
+
+## Changes
+
+- Added `tests/t1100-commit-tree-options.sh` as a harness-compatible port.
+- Added `t1100-commit-tree-options.sh` to `tests/harness/selected-tests.txt`.
+- Updated `gust/src/commands/commit_tree.rs`:
+  - normalize `GIT_AUTHOR_DATE` / `GIT_COMMITTER_DATE` into Git-style `"<unix> <tz>"` when input is:
+    - `@<unix>`, `@<unix> <tz>`, `<unix>`, `<unix> <tz>`
+    - human `YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM` / `YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS`
+    - ISO-8601 datetime forms
+  - retained fallback behavior for unsupported date strings.
+
+## Validation
+
+- `cargo fmt` ✅
+- `cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings` ✅
+- `cargo test --workspace` ✅
+- `./tests/harness/run.sh` ✅
+  - `t0001-init.sh`: 9/9
+  - `t1100-commit-tree-options.sh`: 5/5
